FORMULA
  after each executed query, update public.auto_index_column_stats for the table columns
  total_count means total predicate-column accesses processed for this table so far
  per query: total_count += number of predicate columns referenced by that query
  access_count is read only from the PostgreSQL-collected stats table, never precomputed from queries.sql before execution
  eligible_column = access_count / total_count > max(0.05, 2/total_columns) AND distinct_count / row_count > 0.00
  candidate selection does not require the column to appear in the current query
  skip HypoPG if a real single-column index already exists on that column; evaluate remaining columns
  explain_baseline_scan_cost = EXPLAIN cost with no hypothetical index, logged for comparison
  hypo_scan_cost = EXPLAIN cost after hypopg_reset() + hypopg_create_index(candidate), logged for comparison
  baseline_cost = relpages*seq_page_cost + rows*cpu_tuple_cost
  create_cost = relpages*seq_page_cost + rows*cpu_tuple_cost + rows*index_columns*cpu_operator_cost + rows*log2(rows)*cpu_operator_cost
  expected_without_index = access_count * baseline_cost
  expected_with_index = create_cost + access_count * hypo_scan_cost
  create real index when expected_with_index < expected_without_index

